{"questionId":"27767","questionHtml":"<p>Prove by mathematical induction that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>q</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mi>q</mi></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>consider&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mi>n</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;(reference to part (c)) and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><mi>i</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>assume true for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>, (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mi>k</mi></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>for statements such as “let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>” or “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> is true”. Subsequent marks after this <em><strong>M1</strong></em> are independent of this mark and can be awarded.</p>\n<p><br>consider&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award the above <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>if&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>f</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>k</mi></msub><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;(or equivalent) is stated.</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo largeop=\"true\">Σ</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mi>n</mi></munderover><msup><mi>i</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>i</mi></msup></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>2</mn><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>3</mn><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>since true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math> if true for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math>, hence true for all&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> To obtain the final <em><strong>R1</strong></em>, three of the previous five marks must have been awarded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27767","referenceCode":"22N.3.AHL.TZ0.1d.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Prove by mathematical induction that fqx=Σi=1niqxi, q∈ℤ+.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}